---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Avorix System — Not Just an App."
  description="Three building blocks, one goal: software, training, and staff work together at Avorix. Learn how the system makes your kitchen independent of individual chefs."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-500 mb-4 block">
        The Avorix System
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        Not Just an App.<br />A Complete Kitchen System.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Three building blocks, one goal: a kitchen that keeps your standards, no matter who's at the stove.
        Software, training, and staff work together at Avorix. That's why it works.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/en/contact"
        data-cta-location="system-hero"
        class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-brand-200"
      >
        Book a Demo
      </a>
      <p class="text-sm text-avorix-silver mt-4">Official staff leasing permit</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three Building Blocks -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-4">
        Our System. The Training. The Reinforcement.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Three building blocks that deliver value individually — and together build a kitchen that works independently of individual chefs.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Block 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200 hover:border-brand-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brand-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 18h.01M8 21h8a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H8a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0 002 2z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Our System (the Cook App)</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            The memory of your kitchen. Every recipe is documented step by step — with photos,
            quantities, and time schedules. New employees cook at the level your guests expect from day one.
            No knowledge is lost when someone leaves.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- Block 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200 hover:border-brand-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brand-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.746 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.246 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            The transfer. An Avorix chef comes to your kitchen, enters your recipes into the system, and
            trains your team — not in theory, but directly at the stove. Your team learns to work with the system
            and understands why every step is the way it is.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- Block 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200 hover:border-brand-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-brand-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Reinforcement</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Permanently employed Avorix chefs you can book by the day or week — for bottlenecks,
            seasonal peaks, or transition periods. Every Avorix chef knows the system and can execute your recipes
            immediately, without onboarding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 text-center mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto italic">
        Think of fire prevention and the fire department: the app is fire prevention — it prevents the emergency.
        The reinforcement is the fire department — it comes when things are burning. The training brings both together.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Better Together -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-4">
        Good Individually. Unbeatable Together.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Why isn't a single building block enough?
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm shrink-0">a</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">App only, without training?</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Then you have a tool nobody uses. The best software is worthless if your team doesn't understand why and how to work with it. Without training, the app remains an expensive notebook.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm shrink-0">b</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Training only, without app?</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Then it works — as long as everyone remembers. But knowledge fades, employees change, and after three months you're back to square one. Without a system that stores the knowledge, training is a flash in the pan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm shrink-0">c</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Temp chefs only, without system?</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Then you get a good chef who doesn't know how your kitchen works. Without documented recipes, every temp chef needs a long onboarding — and the results vary.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12 2l3.09 6.26L22 9.27l-5 4.87 1.18 6.88L12 17.77l-6.18 3.25L7 14.14 2 9.27l6.91-1.01L12 2z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">All three together?</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The system stores your knowledge. The training anchors it in the team. The reinforcement steps in when it gets tight — and works at your level immediately, because everything is documented. This creates a kitchen that no longer depends on individuals.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Four Steps -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-4">
        From First Conversation to a Kitchen That Always Works.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-14">
        Four steps — transparent and predictable.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl mx-auto mb-5">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Visit the kitchen</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">We come by, get to know your business, and understand how your kitchen runs today — what works well and where it struggles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl mx-auto mb-5">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Document the menu</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">An Avorix chef enters your recipes into the system — step by step, with photos, quantities, and time schedules. Your kitchen knowledge is digitally secured.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl mx-auto mb-5">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Team learns the system</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Your team is trained directly at the stove — not theory, but practice. Everyone learns to work with the app and maintain the standards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-brand-500 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl mx-auto mb-5">4</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Work independently</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Your kitchen runs. New employees find their way immediately. During bottlenecks, book Avorix reinforcement — no onboarding needed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="system-ablauf" class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-brand-200">Book a Demo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Target Market -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-4">
        Built for Businesses with a Fixed Menu.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Avorix works best where dishes repeat and consistency matters.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-10">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Ideal for:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              Resort hotels with half-board (3- to 5-course menus)
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              Inns and restaurants with a seasonal but stable menu
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              Businesses with high turnover or seasonal staff
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              Houses that want to secure quality without depending on a single head chef
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Honestly, not ideal for:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
              </svg>
              Fine-dining establishments that reinvent their menu daily
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
              </svg>
              Kitchens built around the creative signature of a single chef
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
              </svg>
              Businesses with no interest in standardization
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs mt-4 italic">
            We'd rather say this upfront — so neither of us wastes time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-4">
        What Does It Cost?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Transparent and predictable — no hidden costs.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10 border border-neutral-200 shadow-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Each building block has a clear price, and you get it in black and white during the first call.
          We don't list prices on the website because the scope depends on your menu, your team size, and
          your need for reinforcement. But we promise: no surprises, no hidden fees.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          In the first call, you'll learn exactly what each building block costs — itemized, transparent, and
          comparable. You decide afterwards whether and how you want to start.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="system-kosten" class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors text-center">Book a Demo</a>
          <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="system-pilot" class="inline-block border border-brand-300 text-brand-600 px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors text-center">Pilot Program</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-10">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Can I book just the app, without training and staff?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            Yes, you can. However, we recommend at least the introductory training so your team actually uses the system. In our experience, the app alone delivers only a fraction of the value — the transfer to the team makes the difference.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Can I book just staff, without the app?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            In principle, yes. But: without documented recipes, every temp chef needs onboarding and the results vary more. With the system, our chefs work at your level immediately — that's the whole point.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Our recipes are already documented. Do we still need the training?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            If your recipes already exist in a format your team uses daily — great. Then we can import the data and focus the training on system usage. In practice, we often find that existing documentation is incomplete or gathering dust. We'll clarify that in the first call.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            How long does the implementation take?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            That depends on the size of your menu. For a typical half-board menu with 40-60 dishes, we estimate 2-4 weeks until everything is in the system and your team is trained. After that, you work independently.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            What happens after 12 months?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 shrink-0 ml-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            Your recipes and your knowledge belong to you — always. After 12 months, you can renew the contract, adjust individual building blocks, or pause. There are no lock-in contracts. If the system works, you stay voluntarily.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
        See the System for Yourself. No Obligation.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        30 minutes that bring clarity. We'll show you what the system would look like in your kitchen — concrete, honest, no sales pressure.
      </p>
      <a href="/en/contact" data-cta-location="system-final" class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-brand-200">Book a Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
